{"id":360153,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nicholas_and_Alexandra","text":"\"Nicholas and Alexandra\" is a 1971 biographical movie. It tells the story of the last Russian monarch, Tsar Nicholas II of Russia, and his wife, Tsarina Alexandra.\nThe movie was made from the book by Robert K. Massie. It was directed by Franklin J. Schaffner.\nIt won Academy Awards for Best Art Direction-Set Decoration (John Box, Ernest Archer, Jack Maxsted, Gil Parrondo, Vernon Dixon) and Best Costume Design. It was nominated for Best Actress in a Leading Role (Janet Suzman), Best Cinematography, Best Music, Original Dramatic Score and Best Picture.\nSoundtrack.\nThis soundtrack was written by Richard Rodney Bennett.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Biography","surface_form":"biographical","offset":35},{"uri":"Nicholas_II_of_Russia","surface_form":"Nicholas II of Russia","offset":108},{"uri":"Alexandra_Feodorovna_(Alix_of_Hesse)","surface_form":"Alexandra","offset":153},{"uri":"Nicholas_and_Alexandra_(book)","surface_form":"book","offset":192},{"uri":"Robert_K._Massie","surface_form":"Robert K. Massie","offset":200},{"uri":"Franklin_J._Schaffner","surface_form":"Franklin J. Schaffner","offset":237},{"uri":"Academy_Award","surface_form":"Academy Award","offset":267},{"uri":"Academy_Award_for_Best_Art_Direction","surface_form":"Best Art Direction-Set Decoration","offset":286},{"uri":"John_Box","surface_form":"John Box","offset":321},{"uri":"Ernest_Archer","surface_form":"Ernest Archer","offset":331},{"uri":"Jack_Maxsted","surface_form":"Jack Maxsted","offset":346},{"uri":"Gil_Parrondo","surface_form":"Gil Parrondo","offset":360},{"uri":"Vernon_Dixon","surface_form":"Vernon Dixon","offset":374},{"uri":"Academy_Award_for_Costume_Design","surface_form":"Best Costume Design","offset":392},{"uri":"Academy_Award_for_Best_Actress","surface_form":"Best Actress in a Leading Role","offset":434},{"uri":"Janet_Suzman","surface_form":"Janet Suzman","offset":466},{"uri":"A